All claim terminology has been replaced with "Signed Statement" including the Architecture Diagram.

Please have a look!

@hannestschofenig We should do two approaches, rather than blanket removal:

Option 1) My preferred Option: Somewhere in the Architecture text we refer to some known use cases and link it to the new document. Completely removing use case reference is not a good idea.

Option 2) Retain the title # Use Cases and on the next line refer to the reference to the new document

@hannestschofenig : As the Main heading for the section is `Signed Statement Issuance, Registration, and Verification`

I think, it makes sense to introduce this section as `Signed Statement Envelope` The reason been (a) We are not discussing Issuance per say here

(b) We do not have a fixed signed statement format, but we just have an Envelope which contains a `Payload`

@rjb4standards in COSE and JOSE, there are names like "iss" and "sub" that are already registered in iana, and there are "private names" like "vendor_branding_info", that are not registered.

Registered names are established by updating the registries which requires publishing documents usually.

Private names are ones that people decided to use, without registering them.

